  <h1>Guide for AI Tools</h1>
  <p class="lead">This page explains how AI tools can effectively parse and utilize the educational content on this site.</p>

  <section id="site-overview">
    <h2>Site Architecture Overview</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Cixin Course Weaver (慈心課程織圖)</strong> is a static educational website built with Eleventy (11ty),
      Waldorf's bilingual course archive, connecting lesson goals with teaching artifacts, media folders, and downloads for planners and partners.
    </p>

    <h3>Main Page Structure</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Home (<code>/</code>)</strong>: Site introduction, search portal, and course highlights</li>
      <li><strong>Language Pages</strong>:
        <ul>
          <li><code>/zh-TW/</code> - Traditional Chinese homepage</li>
          <li><code>/en-US/</code> - English homepage</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li><strong>All Courses (<code>/courses/</code>)</strong>: Complete course catalog with filtering by grade, domain, and teacher</li>
      <li><strong>Course Pages (<code>/courses/{slug}/</code>)</strong>: Each course includes:
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Main Pages:</strong>
            <ul>
              <li><code>/courses/{slug}/</code> - Course homepage (overview, learning objectives, teacher bio, downloadable materials)</li>
              <li><code>/courses/{slug}/workbook/</code> - Student workbook photos with tag filtering</li>
              <li><code>/courses/{slug}/photos/</code> - Classroom photo gallery with tag filtering</li>
              <li><code>/courses/{slug}/blackboard/</code> - Blackboard drawing artwork with tag filtering</li>
              <li><code>/courses/{slug}/scripts/</code> - Play script performance photos with tag filtering</li>
              <li><code>/courses/{slug}/songs/</code> - Songs and audio recordings with inline playback</li>
              <li><code>/courses/{slug}/videos/</code> - Video performances (YouTube embeds)</li>
              <li><code>/courses/{slug}/sheet-music/</code> - Sheet music PDFs with preview</li>
              <li><code>/courses/{slug}/syllabus/</code> - Course syllabus PDFs with preview</li>
              <li><code>/courses/{slug}/worksheet/</code> - Student worksheet PDFs with preview</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><strong>Google Docs Content Pages:</strong>
            <ul>
              <li><code>/courses/{slug}/description/</code> - Course description from Google Doc</li>
              <li><code>/courses/{slug}/story/</code> - Story content from Google Doc</li>
              <li><code>/courses/{slug}/play-script/</code> - Play script from Google Doc</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li><strong>Reflections (<code>/reflections/</code>)</strong>: Community discussion forum</li>
      <li><strong>AI-Specific Pages</strong>:
        <ul>
          <li><code>/for-ai/</code> - This guide for AI tools</li>
          <li><code>/ai-index.json</code> - Complete course catalog with full text content</li>
          <li><code>/feed.json</code> - Course update timeline (JSON Feed format)</li>
          <li><code>/sitemap.xml</code> - Complete site sitemap</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="data-structure">
    <h2>Data Structure</h2>

    <h3>Course Metadata</h3>
    <p>Each course is stored as <code>course_*.json</code> in <code>src/_data/</code>, containing:</p>

    <pre><code>{
  "slug": "unique-course-identifier",
  "metadata": { "grade_level": "4", "domain_category": "main-lesson", "teacher_name": "lin-qianyi" },
  "i18n": {
    "zh-TW": { "title": "課程名稱", "overview": "..." },
    "en-US": { "title": "Course Name", "overview": "..." }
  },
  "material": {
    "workbook_photos": [
      { "type": "drive-folder", "id": "FOLDER_ID", "title": "Workbook Photos", "items": [] }
    ],
    "videos": [
      { "type": "youtube", "id": "YOUTUBE_ID", "title": "Performance" }
    ]
  },
  "docs": {
    "course_description": { "type": "google-doc", "id": "DOC_ID" },
    "play_script": { "type": "google-doc", "id": "DOC_ID" }
  }
}</code></pre>

    <h3>Tagging System</h3>
    <p>Images are automatically tagged with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Course-level metadata</strong>: grade, semester, unit, domain</li>
      <li><strong>Filename extraction</strong>: <code>[square brackets]</code>, <code>【fullwidth】</code>, <code>#hashtags</code></li>
      <li><strong>Purpose</strong>: Quick filtering and categorical browsing</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

