  <section id="ci-ai-generation">
    <h3>What's Included in <code>ai-index.json</code></h3>
    <p>The AI index now contains complete Drive-synced content:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Google Docs full text</strong> (<code>docs.course_description.content</code>, <code>docs.play_script.content</code>): Plain text extracted from Google Docs, ideal for semantic search and RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)</li>
      <li><strong>Image metadata</strong> (<code>driveContent.workbook_photos</code>, <code>driveContent.blackboard</code>, <code>driveContent.photos</code>): File IDs, names, tags, and multiple URL formats (thumbnail, preview, direct view)</li>
      <li><strong>Audio file metadata</strong> (<code>driveContent.songs_audio</code>): Audio file names, tags, MIME types, and stream/download URLs</li>
      <li><strong>PDF documents</strong> (<code>driveContent.sheet_music</code>, <code>driveContent.play_scripts</code>): Sheet music and script PDFs with viewer URLs</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="content-types">
    <h2>Content Types & Processing Recommendations</h2>

    <h3>Text Content</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Course descriptions</strong>: Teaching philosophy, thematic explanations, learning objectives</li>
      <li><strong>Teacher bios</strong>: Background, teaching style</li>
      <li><strong>Google Docs integration</strong>: Some courses include full document content</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Visual Materials</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Workbooks</strong>: Student learning process records</li>
      <li><strong>Blackboard drawings</strong>: Teacher chalkboard art</li>
      <li><strong>Photo galleries</strong>: Classroom activities and events</li>
      <li><strong>Script photos</strong>: Drama performance documentation</li>
    </ul>
    <p>⚠️ All images are hosted on Google Drive; public access permissions required.</p>

    <h3>Audio Content</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Formats</strong>: Primarily M4A, MP3</li>
      <li><strong>Types</strong>: Course songs, recitations, instrument performances</li>
      <li><strong>Access</strong>: Stream or download via Google Drive API</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>PDF Documents</h3>
    <p>Many course materials are in PDF format, including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Worksheets</strong> (<code>driveContent.worksheet</code>): Student exercise templates, note-taking formats</li>
      <li><strong>Sheet Music</strong> (<code>driveContent.sheet_music</code>): Musical scores and notation</li>
      <li><strong>Play Scripts</strong> (<code>driveContent.play_scripts</code>): Drama performance scripts</li>
      <li><strong>Syllabi</strong> (<code>driveContent.syllabus</code>): Course outlines and learning plans</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-500 p-4 my-4">
      <p class="font-semibold">PDF Accessibility for AI Tools</p>
      <p><strong>PDF Text Extraction Implemented!</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>✅ <strong>Native PDF support</strong>: Text extraction from PDF files using <code>pdf-parse</code> library</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>Google Docs support</strong>: Text export via Drive API for Google Doc format</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>Automatic caching</strong>: Extracted text stored separately from course JSON</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>AI-ready output</strong>: Full PDF text included in <code>ai-index.json</code></li>
      </ul>

      <p><strong>Limitations:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>⚠️ <strong>Scanned PDFs</strong>: Cannot extract text from image-only PDFs (no text layer)</li>
        <li>⚠️ <strong>File size</strong>: Large PDFs increase <code>ai-index.json</code> size</li>
      </ul>

      <p><strong>What AI Can Access:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>✅ PDF metadata: filename, tags, MIME type</li>
        <li>✅ PDF URLs: for preview and download</li>
        <li>✅ PDF text content: full extracted text in <code>pdfText</code> field</li>
        <li>✅ Sync timestamp: <code>pdfTextLastSynced</code> for freshness tracking</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="usage-guidelines">
    <h2>AI Usage Guidelines</h2>

    <h3>Recommended Tools & Methods</h3>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-4 my-4">
      <p class="font-semibold">NotebookLM</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Add source: Select "Website"</li>
        <li>Paste course URL (e.g., <code>{{ site.url }}/courses/2a-nenggao-113-summer/</code>)</li>
        <li>NotebookLM will crawl the page and linked content</li>
        <li>Example query: "What are the learning objectives of this course?"</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-500 p-4 my-4">
      <p class="font-semibold">ChatGPT / Claude</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Download <code>{{ site.url }}/ai-index.json</code></li>
        <li>Upload the JSON file to the AI chat</li>
        <li>Ask questions like: "Analyze the teaching philosophy in the Mt. Nenggao course based on the teacher's description"</li>
        <li>The AI can access full Google Docs text, image lists, and audio file metadata</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <h3>Sample Queries</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>"Analyze the teaching strategies in Grade 2 nature main lesson"</li>
      <li>"Compare the evolution of blackboard drawing styles across grade levels"</li>
      <li>"How does the drama course integrate Indigenous Taiwanese culture?"</li>
      <li>"What learning processes are reflected in the workbooks?"</li>
      <li>"List all songs used in the Mt. Nenggao drama course"</li>
      <li>"Extract keywords from the play script and course description"</li>
    </ul>

